      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2008-12-10</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2008-12-12T22:36:46Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Systematic Foreclosure Prevention and Mortgage Modification Act - Directs the Chairperson of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation (FDIC) to establish a systematic foreclosure prevention and mortgage modification program by: (1) paying mortgage servicers $1,000 to cover expenses for each loan modified according to specified standards; and (2) sharing up to 50% of any losses incurred if a modified loan should subsequently re-default.</p> <p> </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
